column60: Shotting starts Nov. 19 [at] 7:50pm - South to North, all 70 [degrees?] East. No trail left behind it

column9: Snow still on the ground. Slight aurora

column59: Slight aurora in evening. Stars very bright

About the beginning of the month a small brig left here for Oporto, and was telegraphed as having arrived there on the 12th day after her departure from here - Even 21 days is considered a good passage generally. - at the end of the month a brig arrived here 90 days out from Sicily. - This will give some idea of the weather of late on the Atlantic
3 PM mock sun, northern side of sun
The harbour, (landlocked) has been frozen over for some time: but at this date, the ice about a foot thick, thicker than
column60: anytime this winter. I walked out [] the monthly mail steamer from Halifax, N. S. She put on full presence of steam and charged the ice, advancing about 2 1/2 ship lengths each time. The ice was quite firm right up to the ship's side, whoch I could touch with my hand - The steamer had received some damage from the severe weather.

column59: and morning of the 27th the fire glowed very much
Snow still on ground every day of the month
